stand for redundant array of independent disk green and red light in server if one fail another is working
  also have 2 internet connection and 2 power supply
types of RAID
RAID 0 has no duplicate data
data is lost due to speed
RAID 1
each disk have same data and it has duplicate copy data has been copied more than one disk
RAID 5
data is not duplicate but striped multiple disk along with parity ( is used to rebuild the data)
3,4 tetrabytes will be used for actual data
RAID 10 
it is cominabination of RAID1 and RAID 0 is called RAID 10
you need minimum 4 disk
yu can use 50% data for storage
